==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Philanthropist
<hw>Phi*lan"thro*pist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>fila`nqrwpos</grk>; <grk>fi`los</grk> loving +
<grk>'a`nqrwpos</grk> man: cf. F. <ets>philanthrope</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>One who practices philanthropy; one who loves mankind,
and seeks to promote the good of others; especially, a wealthy
individual who donates large amounts of money to charitable or
philanthropic causes. Opposite of <ant>misanthrope</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Philanthropistic</ent>⟦br⟧
